narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Well, if you're an astronomy major, you have to do it, so I only recommend picking a topic you really like to work on. (duh!)

If you're an astronomy major or an astronomy and physics major, you have to take this course for your senior project. I would recommend that you take the greatest amount of care in choosing your adviser and your project. It's very difficult to see how things will turn out in the months ahead of picking, but if you are left with a very demanding adviser and a difficult project, you will not be happy for much of your senior year. If you do your research about the projects going on in the department, talk to others who have already finished their projects, and are willing to speak frankly and honestly with your adviser, your project will go well.
